description.plain: “I love you but I need another year” is a song about being in denial of needing help. Liza recognises her  symptoms but doesn’t know how to address them and tells her lover that she “just needs another year” to get herself together, scared that they’ll leave her due to her emotional turmoil.

Liza recognises her  symptoms but doesn’t know how to address them and tells her lover that she “just needs another year” to get herself together, scared that they’ll leave her due to her emotional turmoil.

annotations: I know I love you but I need another year

The title of the song appears to be a reference to the Catfish and the Bottlemen song “7”, specifically the chorus:

”I’d beg you but you know I’m never home,
I love you but I need another year alone”

You’re sticking around but how can you stand it?
 I can’t salvage your mind while I’m losing mine quick
 And nobody should have to deal with this
 But I need ya, I don’t wanna leave ya
Again, she is afraid of burdening her lover and doesn’t want them to feel as if they should fix or babysit her
Is I’m not running toward the safest thing
Liza is employing unhealthy coping mechanisms to deal with her emotions but knows they will lead her down a dark path

I don’t want a diagnosis
 I don’t want a name to call this
She’s scared of acknowledging the basis of the problem and the possibility of a mental illness she will be labelled with for the rest of her life.

Stay here
 I know I love you but I need another year, oh
 I don’t wanna drag you through it
Liza tries to assure her lover that she does care about them, she just needs time to fix herself and is scared of affecting them with her own problems.

I don’t think enough
 Before I say too much
 I’m digging my own grave
 With all the shit I say
Liza speaks on impulse, resulting in her saying things she regrets that get her trouble.

body.plain: The official lyrics for this song are deliberately capitalized in some areas of an otherwise lower-case song, spelling out the message “I spend so much time beside myself, want to inhabit my body,” which further contributes to the feeling the singer has of dissociation from her own corporeal vessel.

annotations: And I hate that I can be seen like this

One of the things that can worsen panic attacks is the social stigma around mental health. Oftentimes, the person having a panic attack becomes more panicked about being seen and notices, which Liza Anne describes here.

Think slowly, try to remember I’m alive
 My body is here and I am inside

Grounding techniques are often used in the midst of a panic attack. The purpose of grounding techniques is to allow a person to step away from negative thoughts or flashbacks.

A commonly used grounding technique for anxiety is the 5-4-3-2-1 tactic, in which a person identifies tangible things around them to help ground them in a moment.
I guess I’ve been having trouble sleeping

Anxiety is often correlated with sleep. According to the National Sleep Association, “anxiety is frequently connected to sleeping problems. Excess worry and fear make it harder to fall asleep and stay asleep through the night. Sleep deprivation can worsen anxiety, spurring a negative cycle involving insomnia and anxiety disorders.”
I’m fading in and out of consciousness

An unconscious coping mechanism for panic attacks and other forms of trauma is dissociation.

Dissociation is defined as “the disconnection or separation of something from something else or the state of being disconnected” and is often described as feeling separated from an individual’s conciousness.

My words disappear on a dry tongue
 And I am trying to let you know it
 But I am drowning by the moment
By saying this she means that she wants people to understand her problems and help her to get out of this situation and depression, but it won’t happen so she keeps sinking and getting depressed.
My eyes move slowly side to side

This could refer to EMDR (EMDR: Eye Movement Desensitization and Reprocessing) which can be used to treat panic attacks. It involves the the patient moving their eyes from side to side while recalling distressing images or memories.
Oh God, tell me is it over yet?
Even though you know you’re “fine” it doesn’t much help in that moment and you just hope it’s over soon.

I think I wanna die
 But I guess I know I’m fine

When you’re having a panic attack you want it to be over, sometimes so badly that you wish you were dead (especially when you’re tired of having panic attacks) even though you actually know nothing is really wrong with you.

body.plain: The second single off Liza Anne’s 2020 album Bad Vacation, Bummer Days sees her pondering her lack of knowledge about where to go next, and her own ability to make herself feel sad when she wants to feel good.

annotations: I spent the last two years in shoes that were too big
Depression can make it nearly impossible for people to get things done. She has spent two years in shoes that were too big because she never found the energy to return them or get new ones.
But I get off on all my bummer days

Much of Liza’s songs is about her struggle with Anxiety and depression. This could be referring to how her “bummer days,” days when she’s feeling especially anxious or sad, are inspiration for her music.

I say I wanna wake up with the dawn
 But every night I sleep with the shades drawn

Those with depression will usually say things like, “tomorrow’s the day I will change my routine” and want to stop the cycle of sadness they’re living in, but they never do because it’s not that easy.

“Paranoia” was the first single released for Liza Anne’s 2018 album Fine But Dying. She made her television debut on February 6, 2018, performing the song on Conan.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Bm060Z1qfpU

annotations: Brush it under the bed, another time but it won’t stay down

“Brush it under the bed” is a phrase that means ignoring something or refusing to talk about it. Her partner is refusing to address her anxiety and tells her “she’ll be fine” but for anything to change, you actually have to talk about it.

Say how you wish I could feel
 Like the others, another lover that you had before

Those with anxiety will often doubt that their partners really love them and worry that their anxiety makes them a “burden.” This is her thinking that her partner must wish she was like his past lovers that didn’t struggle like she does.
Running water in the bathroom
When people have panic attacks, they will often run cold water on their face or hands to try to calm down or feel less numb
I can’t get rid of it ’cause killing it’s like pulling my own teeth
Anxiety is something that is impossible to get rid of. It’s always there.
It’s 3 AM and I can’t sleep, I don’t even recognize me
With Anxiety disorders, one can get awful panic attacks late at night.
